28
00:05:25.547 --> 00:05:26.997
The dream?

29
00:05:30.886 --> 00:05:33.253
You're my only dream.

30
00:05:38.593 --> 00:05:42.062
Will you ever
tell me what you see?

31
00:05:43.348 --> 00:05:46.232
I see only
my lovely Petra.

32
00:05:50.105 --> 00:05:51.821
Oh. please.

33
00:05:51.907 --> 00:05:54.574
How can you desire such a cow?

34
00:05:54.609 --> 00:05:57.444
Oh. but a beautiful cow it is.

35
00:06:01.667 --> 00:06:03.416
Oh. he kicks fierce

36
00:06:03.452 --> 00:06:05.869
as his father
this morning.

37
00:06:05.954 --> 00:06:07.787
How do you know it's a he?

38
00:06:07.873 --> 00:06:09.289
Annora insists

39
00:06:09.341 --> 00:06:12.008
your firstborn will be an heir.

40
00:06:12.094 --> 00:06:14.377
Ah. we're taking divine council

41
00:06:14.463 --> 00:06:16.379
from the Slavic witch now.
are we?

42
00:06:16.465 --> 00:06:18.798
She's a healer. not a witch.

43
00:06:18.884 --> 00:06:22.135
Her herbs help
my weakness and sleep.

44
00:06:22.220 --> 00:06:23.887
And the silent hooded one--
does he offer

45
00:06:23.972 --> 00:06:25.472
dirt scratch visions
of our son's fate?

46
00:06:25.524 --> 00:06:26.523
Yea.

47
00:06:26.608 --> 00:06:28.274
Insists he'll be as pious

48
00:06:28.310 --> 00:06:31.194
and mule-headed as his father.

49
00:06:31.279 --> 00:06:32.779
I'm not mule-headed.

50
00:06:32.814 --> 00:06:34.698
- I just devote to the thing at hand.
- Good.

51
00:06:34.783 --> 00:06:36.366
Get your breeches up

52
00:06:36.451 --> 00:06:38.151
and devote to filling
the barrels.

53
00:06:38.203 --> 00:06:40.120
We're near out of water.

54
00:06:40.155 --> 00:06:41.988
Think that would be a task
for a strong cow.

55
00:06:48.463 --> 00:06:49.662
Oh.

56
00:06:49.715 --> 00:06:51.331
Oh. no! Oh!

57
00:06:53.635 --> 00:06:54.467
Ooh!

58
00:07:05.097 --> 00:07:13.436
_

59
00:07:34.509 --> 00:07:36.760
I'm sure they're wasted seeds.

60
00:07:36.845 --> 00:07:38.711
Like the rest.

61
00:07:41.016 --> 00:07:44.884
God will bestow us with a child
in his time. Erik.

62
00:07:44.970 --> 00:07:47.887
Then let God waste his hours

63
00:07:47.939 --> 00:07:50.440
chasing a barren hole
with swollen meat.

64
00:08:10.162 --> 00:08:11.661
Come.

65
00:08:20.255 --> 00:08:21.554
Morning. Baroness.

66
00:08:23.725 --> 00:08:25.558
Morning.

67
00:08:50.836 --> 00:08:52.785
Should I draw a bath. milady?

68
00:08:52.838 --> 00:08:56.339
I need more than a bath.

69
00:08:56.424 --> 00:08:59.259
sweet Isabel.

70
00:09:05.267 --> 00:09:07.100
So much more.

71
00:09:17.879 --> 00:09:22.319
♪ born with a heart ♪

72
00:09:22.897 --> 00:09:28.240
♪ that could ache
more than beat ♪

73
00:09:30.292 --> 00:09:36.162
♪ the mind of a killer ♪

74
00:09:36.214 --> 00:09:39.999
♪ the soul of the meek ♪

75
00:09:42.554 --> 00:09:48.174
♪ flock with no shepherd ♪

76
00:09:48.226 --> 00:09:54.280
♪ is a vulnerable game ♪

77
00:09:54.349 --> 00:09:57.183
♪ I can live
without a hearth ♪

78
00:09:57.235 --> 00:10:00.520
♪ without love ♪

79
00:10:00.572 --> 00:10:04.574
♪ but I do need a name ♪

80
00:10:07.329 --> 00:10:09.913
♪ Father. do you burn ♪

81
00:10:09.998 --> 00:10:13.416
♪ if your hand is in fire? ♪

82
00:10:13.501 --> 00:10:16.502
♪ does your head
spin with rage ♪

83
00:10:16.571 --> 00:10:20.006
♪ when fooled by the liars? ♪

84
00:10:20.075 --> 00:10:25.612
♪ King of the kings ♪

85
00:10:25.680 --> 00:10:30.266
♪ do you feel any pain? ♪

86
00:10:31.853 --> 00:10:34.602
♪ do you feel any pain? ♪

87
00:10:35.032 --> 00:10:37.589
